               wetlands is reoxidised in their aerobic zones (rhizosphere and
               oxidised soil-water interface). Methane consumption occurs in
               most soils and exhibits a broad range of values. Highest
               consumption rates or potentials are observed in soils where
               methanogenesis is or has been effective and where CH4
               concentration is or has been much higher than in the atmosphere
               (ricefields, swamps, landfills, etc.). Aerobic soils consume
               atmospheric CH4 but their activities are very low and the
