               Jennifer S",
  abstract  = "Rates of ecosystem nitrogen (N) cycling may be mediated by the
               presence of ectomycorrhizal fungi, which compete directly with
               free-living microbes for N. In the regenerating tropical dry
               forests of Central America, the distribution of ectomycorrhizal
               trees is affected by succession and soil parent material, both
               of which may exert independent influence over soil N fluxes. In
               order to quantify these interacting controls, we used a
               scale-explicit sampling strategy to examine soil N cycling at
               scales ranging from the microsite to ecosystem level. We
