               approximately double that for CH4, correctly reflecting the
               stoichiometry of aerobic CH4 oxidation. The CH4 oxidation
               kinetics were used in a mathematical model to examine the effect
               of plant roots on increasing the vertical transport rate of CH4
               out of and O2 into the peat, by gas phase transport through the
